	<p>
	A winding Virginia road.<br>
	An old country back road. <br>
	A road which leads me, <br>
	Home.
	<br> <br>
	Past everlasting trees. <br>
	Past pastures of manure, <br>
	Coloring each a deep green; <br>
	Weathered wooden fences, <br>
	Guide me, on my way, <br>
	Home.
	<br> <br>
	Mountains so high, <br>
	Surely I can reach their unbound skies. <br>
	Skies which surround the place <br>
	I call, <br>
	Home.
	<br> <br>
	Deep blue ponds. <br>
	Fishing hole fools. <br>
	Talking about the one that got away, <br>
	On our way, <br>
	Home.
	<br> <br>
	Back to a place, <br>
	My space. <br>
	A place where I am free, <br>
	Free to be me. <br>
	The place I call, <br>
	Home.
