	<p>
	I sit up, <br>
	against the chair back, <br>
	as the lies stack <br>
	against me, <br>
	I try not to fold <br>
	from the weight <br>
	of words, <br>
	be bold, <br>
	I am told <br>
	to find the courage <br>
	not to lose strength, <br>
	at times <br>
	to lost to walk <br>
	to broken to surrender, <br>
	finding no truth <br>
	in the falsehood of others.
	</p>
